  "prompt": "Why does Peter Thiel hate Gawker?",
  "response": "Peter Thiel's animosity towards Gawker dates back to the site's 2007 article that publicly outed him as gay without his consent. Thiel felt his privacy was violated and viewed Gawker's actions as an example of irresponsible journalism. This event fueled a longstanding grudge against the media company.\n\nIn response, Thiel funded various lawsuits against Gawker, including the infamous invasion of privacy lawsuit filed by former professional wrestler Hulk Hogan. Gawker had published excerpts of a sex tape involving Hogan, leading to the lawsuit. Thiel's support helped Hogan secure a $140 million judgment against Gawker in 2016, a sum that Gawker could not afford, leading to its bankruptcy and eventual closure.\n\nThiel's actions were controversial and sparked debates on topics like press freedom, privacy rights, and the influence of wealthy individuals on media and the legal system.",
